description.en:
This is a knowledge model that aims to provide the taxonomy and  vocabulary to describe the building materials and products,with their corresponding properties and individuals relevant within the construction industry as found within the most commonly used Building Information Modeling (BIM) tools.
This is developed to closely follow the basic Industry Foundation Class (IFC) schema IFC4 ADD2_TC1 so that it can be used for semantic interoperability solutions within the BIM domain

labels.en: Building Information Modelling (BIM) Tools Material Library Ontology

comment.undefined: The building element comprises all elements that are primarily part of the construction of a built facility, i.e., its structural and space separating system. Building elements are all physically existent and tangible things. Major functional part of a building, examples are foundation, floor, roof, wall. (https://standards.buildingsmart.org/IFC/DEV/IFC4_2/FINAL/HTML/schema/ifcproductextension/lexical/ifcbuildingelement.htm)
